 of stable,\nhighly hydrated compounds. We find that Na2SO4, MgCl2 and MgSO4 are most\ncompatible with the non-icy component at the surface of the icy moons as\nobserved by the NIMS instrument on Galileo and by ground-based observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Dec 2021 14:16:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-12"}
